      • getMinAltitude

        public double getMinAltitude()
        Returns the minimum altitude for a geobound and could be the same as the maximum altitude. Please note, this could also be Double.NaN which means the altitude is not valid and should be ignored during calculations.
        Returns:
        the minimum altitude.

      • getMaxAltitude

        Returns:
        the maximum altitude.

                          boolean wrap180,

        Perform intersection between a geobound and a set of values that define a geometry.
        Parameters:
        north - the north value
        west - the west value
        south - the south value
        east - the east value
        wrap180 - if the geometry wraps the IDL line
        minAltitude - the minimum altitude preferably in HAE. If it is NaN, the altitudes will not be used.
        maxAltitude - the maximum altitude preferably in HAE. If it is NaN, the altitudes will not be used.
        Returns:

      • setWrap180

        public void setWrap180​(boolean wrap180)
        Set whether these bounds should wrap around the IDL if the longitudinal span is >180 degrees Should be used for bounds that are typically small
        Parameters:
        wrap180 - True to wrap around backwards False to leave as is (default)
